title: FTC Settlement Won't Change Facebook's Behavior, Commissioner Slaughter Says
text: Rebecca Kelly Slaughter, U.S. Federal Trade Commission commissioner, explains her vote against the FTC's $5 billion settlement with Facebook Inc. She speaks with Bloomberg's Emily Chang on "Bloomberg Technology."

title: Facebook warns investors that Libra digital currency may never see the light of day

title: Facebook And Libra Are Looming Large Over Tomorrow's Crypto Hearing In Congress
text: Congress deserves plaudits for the detailed questions and expansive knowledge that it demonstrated during the Libra hearings last week. However, the next step is to move beyond asking questions and make difficult decisions regarding the tradeoff between innovation and regulation.

title: Companies that use Facebook ‘Like’ button liable for data: EU court
text: Companies that embed Facebook’s “Like” button on their websites allowing users’ personal data to be transferred to the US social network can be held liable for collecting the data, Europe’s top court said on Monday. Website plugins are a common feature of online retail as companies seek to promote their products on popular social networks,.

title: Websites using Facebook 'Like' button liable for data, Europe's top court decides
text: 'Like' button plugins can transmit people's data back to Facebook even if they don't click on those buttons, the ECJ finds.

title: Election Season Is Coming, Buy Facebook And Alphabet
text: As the 2020 election cycle is well underway and the hearts of voters all across the country are sought after by a variety of campaigns, online outreach will set records.
